ODU WEATHER NOTIFICATION
National Weather Service has issued a flash flood watch for the Hampton Roads region, which is in effect tonight through Thursday 
afternoon. Showers may result in 2 to 4 inches of rain, with locally higher amounts possible. Runoff from these showers may cause flash flooding.
While this is not expected to impact Old Dominion Universityâ€™s operating schedule, faculty, staff and students are urged to use 
caution and monitor weather.gov for official storm information and possible changes to the forecast.